The Duke and Duchess of Sussex have just a year to begin the process over allegations made in Mr Bowers book titled Revenge: Meghan, Harry, and the War Between the Windsors.Royal commentator Gareth Russell thinks Meghan and Harry will refrain from correcting claims, while others believe the two will launch yet another lawsuit.Twitter user @missakuaafriyie said: "It’s a week since the release of the book and yet the silence is deafening. I expected @ least a legal warning but nothing. When is the lawsuit."In total, the Sussexes reportedly filed 10 lawsuits in three years in cases involving a series of publishers such as the Mail on Sunday and Rupert Murdoch’s newspaper publisher. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...